<subSubSection id="C358655E86096B2FFA958BC0F9A3F7FE" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586096B2FFA958BC0F9A3F7FE" blockId="27.[1308,2293,1925,3206]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Definition. Shell minute, thin, globose to elongate, narrowly phaneromphalous. Surface smooth except for very weak growth lines. Protoconch deviated, aperture simple, circular.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E86096B2FFA958418F82EF709" box="[1357,1972,2156,2194]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586096B2FFA958418F82EF709" blockId="27.[1308,2293,1925,3206]" box="[1357,1972,2156,2194]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E86096B2FFA9584EEF704F775" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586096B2FFA9584EEF704F775" blockId="27.[1308,2293,1925,3206]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Etymology. This genus is named after my wife Kim to record her contributions throughout this study.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E86096B2FFA958482F9D5F455" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586096B2FFA958482F9D5F455" blockId="27.[1308,2293,1925,3206]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">
Remarks. This genus is similar to recent genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFAC48550FA2CF6D1" box="[1308,1462,2340,2378]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoellidae" genus="Rissoella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786096B2FFAC48550FA2CF6D1" box="[1308,1462,2340,2378]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Rissoella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shell and protoconch characters, and is different from any known Palaeozoic gastropods. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFAC4850BFA52F63D" box="[1308,1480,2431,2470]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoellidae" genus="Rissoella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786096B2FFAC4850BFA52F63D" box="[1308,1480,2431,2470]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Rissoella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is characterised by a simple, sometime deviated protoconch was included tentatively in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFA7985AFF954F598" box="[1441,1742,2523,2563]" order="Heterogastropoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="63" rank="order">Heterogastropoda</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B2486096B2FF8F185AFF758F598" author="Ponder, W. F. &amp; E. K. Yoo" box="[1833,2242,2523,2563]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" pagination="133 - 185" refId="ref27153" refString="Ponder, W. F. &amp; E. K. Yoo, 1977. A revision of the Australian species of the Rissoellidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Records of the Australian Museum 33 (4): 133 - 185." type="journal article" year="1977">Ponder &amp; Yoo (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, a group which shows mixed opisthobranch and prosobranch characters. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B2486096B2FF909864CF827F5C4" author="Climo, F. M." box="[1745,1981,2616,2655]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" pagination="275 - 288" refId="ref24756" refString="Climo, F. M., 1975. The anatomy of Gegania valkyrie Powell (Mollusca: Heterogastropoda: Mathildidae) with notes on other heterogastropods. Royal Society of New Zealand Journal 5 (3): 275 - 288." type="journal article" year="1975">Climo (1975)</bibRefCitation>
has outlined the characteristics of some families of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FF8148611F76FF517" box="[1996,2293,2661,2700]" order="Heterogastropoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="63" rank="order">Heterogastropoda</taxonomicName>
and suggested that the 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FF8C686E7F7F9F521" box="[1822,2147,2707,2746]" order="Heterogastropoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="63" rank="order">Heterogastropoda</taxonomicName>
shows more affinities with opisthobranchs than mesogastropods. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B2486096B2FF8C7869BF769F48D" author="Ponder, W. F. &amp; A Waren" box="[1823,2291,2799,2838]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" pagination="288 - 326" refId="ref27113" refString="Ponder, W. F. &amp; A Waren, 1988. Classification of the Caenogastropoda and Heterostropha a list of the Family group names and higher taxa. Malacologica 1 Review, Supplement 4: 288 - 326." type="journal article" year="1988">Ponder &amp; Waren (1988)</bibRefCitation>
assigned the Heteromorpha to the same rank as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFAAB873FF915F4E9" box="[1395,1679,2891,2930]" pageId="27" pageNumber="96" rank="subClass" subClass="Opisthobranchia">Opisthobranchia</taxonomicName>
under subclass 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FF83C873FF774F4E9" box="[2020,2286,2891,2930]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" rank="subClass" subClass="Heterobranchia">Heterobranchia</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFAC4870DFA3FF404" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1308,1445,2937,2975]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786096B2FFAC4870DFA3FF404" box="[1308,1445,2937,2975]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Kimina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is tentatively included in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686096B2FFAC687DCF9D0F455" box="[1310,1610,2984,3022]" order="Heterogastropoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="63" rank="order">Heterogastropoda</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
